<h1>About</h1>
<p>This site presents the text of <em>Shaar Hayichud</em> ("The Gate of Unity"), the second section of <em>Tanya</em> by Rabbi Schneur Zalman of Liadi, with clearly labeled subsections to make the structure of the argument easy to follow.</p>

<h2>What's Here</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong><a href="/en/texts/">Texts</a></strong> — The Hebrew original, divided into chapters with labeled sections.</li>
  <li><strong><a href="/en/translation/">Translation</a></strong> — An English translation in progress, guided by a philosophy of clarity and idiomatic English.</li>
  <li><strong><a href="/en/classes/">Classes</a></strong> — Audio recordings of classes on Shaar Hayichud.</li>
</ul>

<h2>About the Text</h2>
<p><em>Shaar Hayichud</em> ("The Gate of Unity") was authored by Rabbi Dov Ber of Lubavitch (1773–1827), the Mitteler Rebbe, second leader of Chabad Chassidus.</p>
<p>This work is widely regarded as the key to Kabbalah and Chassidus. Its mastery is considered a prerequisite for all serious students of Kabbalistic and Chassidic thought, because it brings absolute clarity to the entire methodology of Kabbalah and to the process of creation known as the chaining down of the worlds (<em>hishtalshelus</em>). It is therefore the foundation for unlocking the secrets of Kabbalah and the treasure troves of Chassidus — a must-read for any sincere seeker of Divine truth.</p>
